# .cursorrules — Sweet Munchies WordPress ACF Theme

## Design Source of Truth
- Reference the design artifact at https://claude.ai/code/artifact/1c02bcb5-f44b-4b70-8d6d-687c17e185c6?org=41ad3a15-ecd2-4a86-b036-ce0d96dba095 for all visual/structural decisions
- Extracted design folder here - @wp-content/themes/design
- Compare rendered blocks against the design for spacing, colour, typography, responsive behaviour
- Flag any design ambiguities before building (don't guess)

---

## CRITICAL: Build One Block Per Session

All 13 current blocks are built and reviewed — this workflow applies to any NEW block.

### Workflow (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
1. Build ONE block only (ACF registration + template + SCSS + JS if needed)
2. STOP and wait for explicit approval from human
3. Wait for human to review the code, test in wp-admin, verify on mobile/tablet/desktop, confirm the design matches
4. Only after human says "build next" proceed to the next block

### Never Do This
- ❌ Build multiple blocks in one response
- ❌ Assume all blocks follow the same pattern without testing
- ❌ Skip testing/review cycle
- ❌ Auto-commit without human review

---

## Architecture Snapshot

- All page/post content is the ACF flexible content field `content_sections`, rendered by `sweetmunchies_render_flexible_content()` (inc/acf.php). Layout name (underscores) maps to `inc/blocks/{name}.php` (hyphens). The classic editor is removed — pages without blocks render empty.
- **WooCommerce: the theme owns ALL WC markup — no `woocommerce_*` hook soup.** Routing: `woocommerce.php` (theme root) sends shop/category archives to `woocommerce/archive-product.php`; single product renders `woocommerce/content-single-product.php`; the cart is `page-cart.php`. Product cards live in `woocommerce/content-product.php`, shared via `inc/template-parts/product-grid.php`.
- **There is no on-site checkout or account.** Orders are confirmed on WhatsApp (cart builds a `wa.me` message). `/checkout/` and `/my-account/` redirect to the cart (inc/woocommerce.php) — do not build checkout flows or link to those pages.
- Products with an empty price are quote-on-request (POA): no cart form, a WhatsApp enquiry box instead.
- Gift-message add-on (inc/woocommerce-cart.php): +$ surcharge from Theme Settings, message capped at 500 chars (textarea maxlength AND server-side). Quantities are capped at 99 (input `max` AND server-side).
- The cart's nonce-less, session-scoped AJAX endpoints are deliberate — they mirror WC core's own add_to_cart/remove_from_cart convention and are documented in inc/woocommerce-cart.php. Don't "fix" this without discussion.

---

## PHP Standards & Security

### File Headers
Every PHP file starts with `<?php`, then `declare(strict_types=1);`, THEN the file docblock (this order is deliberate — phpcs.xml.dist accounts for it).

### Inside Block Templates
- ONLY `get_sub_field()` inside flexible content loops — NEVER `get_field()` for layout fields. Options are read with `get_field('name', 'option')`.
- Escape at echo time, not at assignment:
  - Text: `esc_html()` · Rich text: `wp_kses_post()` · URLs: `esc_url()` · Attributes: `esc_attr()`
- Deliberately unescaped output requires a `// phpcs:ignore WordPress.Security.EscapeOutput.OutputNotEscaped -- <reason>` on the echo line.
- **Images: always `wp_get_attachment_image($id, $size, false, ['loading' => ..., 'sizes' => ...])`** — never a raw `<img src="$image['url']">` (loses srcset/alt/dimensions). Pick a registered size that matches the rendered slot.

### Defensive patterns (all established in this codebase — keep them)
- `function_exists()` guard around every plugin-provided function (`wpforms()`, `wc_*`)
- `is_wp_error()` check on `get_term_link()` before `esc_url()`
- `get_field(..., 'option') ?: []` — option fields return null until the options page is saved once; provide PHP fallbacks for copy too
- Blocks early-return when required data is missing

### Forbidden Actions — STOP & ASK
- Do NOT modify `wp-config.php`, `.htaccess` without explicit approval
- Do NOT create custom post types, taxonomies, or metaboxes
- Do NOT install new plugins
- Do NOT modify git remote URLs or commit version numbers automatically
- Do NOT add inline styles — enumerated choices (e.g. a background_color select) become modifier classes; the ONLY inline-style exception is an editor-uploaded background-image
- Do NOT use `eval()`, `extract()`, or variable variables

---

## Linting & QA (run before calling anything done)

- `composer install` once per machine (installs phpcs + WPCS 3; the `dealerdirect` plugin is allow-listed in composer.json).
- **Every PHP change:** `php -l` on the file AND `vendor/bin/phpcs` must pass clean. A pre-commit hook runs parallel-lint + phpcs on staged PHP files (`git commit --no-verify` to bypass in emergencies). `vendor/bin/phpcbf <file>` auto-fixes most formatting complaints.
- `phpcs.xml.dist` is tuned on purpose: security/escaping/i18n/prefixing/PHP-compat are enforced; wp.org whitespace style (space-padded parens, tabs-only, Yoda, long arrays) is excluded because this codebase is PSR-ish. Don't re-add those sniffs and don't fight the excluded styles.
- **Every SCSS/JS change:** `cd assets && npx gulp build` (ESLint runs inside the JS build; single quotes enforced). `dist/` IS committed on purpose — this deploys to shared hosting with no build step, so rebuild before committing.
- **Verify in the browser after EVERY CSS change, not just the first** — specificity interactions have silently undone earlier fixes here before. Check mobile (390), tablet (768), desktop (1440).
- Local test site: https://localhost/sweetmunchies_wordpresscms/

---

## JavaScript

- Vanilla ES6 modules in `assets/js/lib/`, imported and initialized in `assets/js/main.js` (DOMContentLoaded), bundled by webpack via gulp. Each module early-returns when its root element is absent.
- Configuration flows through `data-*` attributes on the markup — no inline handlers, no localized script objects unless WC provides them.
- **One exception to "no jQuery":** `window.jQuery(document.body).trigger('added_to_cart'|'removed_from_cart', ...)` for WooCommerce fragment interop (header cart badge via wc-cart-fragments). Guard with `if (window.jQuery)`.
- WC's add_to_cart AJAX reports failure as `{error: true}` with HTTP 200 — always check it before showing success.
- Heavy per-block assets (e.g. a carousel lib): register in `sweetmunchies_block_assets()` (functions.php) — they enqueue only on pages using that layout. Do NOT add separate enqueue callbacks.
- No `console.log` in committed code.

---

## SCSS/CSS

### Structure & Tokens
- Block partials in `assets/scss/components/_{block-name}.scss`, `@use`-d in `style.scss`
- Spacing: `--spacer-4/8/16/24/32/48/64/96` — no raw px for spacing
- Colours: `--color-primary` / `--color-primary-dark` (pink CTA + hover), `--color-secondary` (dark green), `--color-white`, tints `--color-pink-tint` / `--color-green-tint` / `--color-cream-alt`, text `--color-text` / `--color-text-muted` (see abstracts/_variables.scss + base/_colors.scss) — no raw hex except rgba() shadows
- Fonts are **self-hosted** (`/fonts/` + `base/_fonts.scss` @font-face, latin subset, `font-display: swap`). Never re-add Google Fonts CDN links, in PHP or SCSS.

### Responsive
- **Mobile-first via the SCSS mixin**: base styles are mobile, then `@include min-breakpoint(mobile|tablet|desktop|wide)` (576 / 768 / 1024 / 1440, defined in abstracts/_mixins.scss)
- Never `max-width` media queries, never hardcoded breakpoint values, and CSS custom properties do NOT work in media queries — use the mixin

### BEM
- `.block`, `.block__element`, `.block--modifier` / `.block__element--modifier`; max nesting depth 2; no utility classes

### Known gotchas (learned the hard way — keep these guards)
- `.xxx-page > .container { padding-top: ... }` ALSO matches the breadcrumb strip — it carries `.container` and is a direct child of the same `<main>`, and the two-class child selector out-specifies the breadcrumb's own modifier. Keep `:not(.page-banner__breadcrumb)` on such selectors.
- The header logo deliberately overhangs below the header bar. Pages without a hero image need the breadcrumb's `--no-hero` top clearance (see _page-banner.scss) — don't reduce it based on the header bar's box alone; check the rendered logo.

---

## ACF

- Field groups live as local JSON in `acf-json/` — when editing JSON directly, bump the group's `"modified"` timestamp so wp-admin offers a sync
- Every field gets an `instructions` line an editor can act on ("Leave empty to hide.", format notes for load-bearing values like the WhatsApp number)
- Repeaters/galleries get min/max when the layout constrains them (trust bar 4, feature grid 6, testimonials 6, hero gallery 2); leave genuinely unbounded lists (FAQ) uncapped
- Flexible content layout slug matches the block template name

---

## Environment Notes

- Local XAMPP PHP has **no webp support in GD** — uploads get zero thumbnail sizes (so no srcset) until regenerated with a webp-capable PHP (Homebrew PHP works: load wp-load.php + `wp_generate_attachment_metadata`). Production hosting with webp GD/Imagick is unaffected, but re-check after bulk local uploads.

---

## Git Commits

- One logical change per commit (one block, one fix batch)
- Commit message format: `feat(blocks): Add [block-name] block with ACF fields` / `fix(...)`, `chore(...)`
- Include PHP + SCSS + rebuilt dist/ in the same commit
- Never auto-bump version numbers
- Never push — I will do it myself

---

## Success Criteria

A change is "done" when:
- ✅ Renders without errors and matches the design artifact (spacing, colours, typography)
- ✅ Responsive at 390 / 768 / 1440, re-verified in the browser after the final edit
- ✅ All output escaped, no inline styles, no console errors
- ✅ `php -l` + `vendor/bin/phpcs` clean, `gulp build` clean
- ✅ Empty/missing-field states handled (block hides or degrades, never fatals)
- ✅ Code reviewed by human (you)
- ✅ Committed with a clear message
